                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/5297.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-21T23:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 21, 1912—11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consul, Vera Cruz, telegraphs October 21, 10 a.m., that Federal commander Beltrán
                    has given notice that he will endeavor to regain possession of Vera Cruz by
                    force of arms within 24 hours from the receipt of his message by the consul.
                    Reiterate to the Mexican Government the hope expressed in the Department’s
                    October 18, 2 p.m., that no fighting which would endanger American life and
                    property will take place. Consul has been instructed to confer with commander of
                        <hi rend="italic">Des Moines</hi> and his colleagues and to take all
                    necessary precautions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
